    <fr:title text="Constrained clause">Constrained clause</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>
  Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal  L]]></fr:tex> be a first-order language. A <html:strong>constrained clause</html:strong> is a formula <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> of the form 
</html:p>
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \phi  \land  \bigvee _{i = 1}^m \neg  X_i(\bf  t_i) \land  \bigvee  _{j = 1}^n Y_j(\bf  s_j)
]]></fr:tex>
    <html:p>
  where:
</html:p>
    <html:ul><html:li>
    (<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi ]]></fr:tex>) is a <html:em>first-order formula</html:em> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex></html:li>
  <html:li>
    (<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X_i, Y_j]]></fr:tex>) are <html:em>predicate variables</html:em>, i.e. denote placeholders for relations
  </html:li>
  <html:li>
    (<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\bf  t_i, \bf  s_j]]></fr:tex>) are <html:em>tuples of terms</html:em> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex></html:li></html:ul>
    <html:p>
  the formula <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> is denoted...
</html:p>
    <html:ul><html:li><html:em>Horn</html:em>, if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n \leq  1]]></fr:tex></html:li>
  <html:li><html:em>dual-Horn</html:em>, if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m \leq  1]]></fr:tex></html:li>
  <html:li><html:em>linear-Horn</html:em>, if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m, n \leq  1]]></fr:tex></html:li></html:ul>
    <html:p>
  commonly we talk about sets of constrained clauses <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>, these sets denote <html:strong>conjunctions</html:strong> of clauses and are thus equivalent to the formula  
</html:p>
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \forall ^* \land _{C \in  S} \equiv  S \triangleq  \{C_1, C_2, \ldots , C_n\}
]]></fr:tex>
    <html:p>
  The formula <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\exists  \bf  X \forall  ^*_{C \in  S} C]]></fr:tex> is called
</html:p>
    <html:ul><html:li>A <html:em>Horn formula</html:em>, if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> is a set of CHC</html:li>
  <html:li>A <html:em>dual-Horn formula</html:em>, if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> is a set of CdHC</html:li>
  <html:li>A <html:em>linear-Horn formula</html:em>, if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> is a set of ClHC</html:li></html:ul>
  </fr:mainmatter>
